Eu(1) is bonded to twelve equivalent O(1) atoms to form EuO12 cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Eu(1)O12 cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Bi(1)O12 cuboctahedra, faces with four equivalent Zr(1)O6 octahedra, and faces with four equivalent Fe(1)O6 octahedra. All Eu(1)–O(1) bond lengths are 2.87 Å. Zr(1) is bonded to six equivalent O(1) atoms to form ZrO6 octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Fe(1)O6 octahedra, faces with four equivalent Eu(1)O12 cuboctahedra, and faces with four equivalent Bi(1)O12 cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Zr(1)–O(1) bond lengths are 2.08 Å. Fe(1) is bonded to six equivalent O(1) atoms to form FeO6 octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Zr(1)O6 octahedra, faces with four equivalent Eu(1)O12 cuboctahedra, and faces with four equivalent Bi(1)O12 cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Fe(1)–O(1) bond lengths are 1.99 Å. Bi(1) is bonded to twelve equivalent O(1) atoms to form BiO12 cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Bi(1)O12 cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Eu(1)O12 cuboctahedra, faces with four equivalent Zr(1)O6 octahedra, and faces with four equivalent Fe(1)O6 octahedra. All Bi(1)–O(1) bond lengths are 2.87 Å. O(1) is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to two equivalent Eu(1), one Zr(1), one Fe(1), and two equivalent Bi(1) atoms.
